cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
title: "unified-gate: Confidence-gated adaptive LLM inference on a 7-dimensional boundary manifold"
authors:
  - family-names: Corcoran
    given-names: Parrish
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/parrishcorcoran/unified-gate"
url: "https://huggingface.co/parrishcorcoran/unified-gate"
abstract: >
  A confidence-gated adaptive LLM inference controller. Twenty physics-inspired features
  feed a 64x64 MLP that decides per token whether to accept a cheap draft or run the
  full backbone. Held-out on BitNet b1.58 2B: 10.6% skip at 95% fidelity, 14.1% skip at
  90% fidelity, replicated across 5 random seeds. The per-sequence intrinsic dimension
  of the per-token difficulty manifold is ~7 for both BitNet 2B and Llama 3.1 8B,
  suggesting a model-agnostic physics ceiling for per-token decision-making.
keywords:
  - language-model
  - inference-efficiency
  - speculative-decoding
  - medusa
  - bitnet
  - adaptive-compute
  - intrinsic-dimension
version: "0.2.0"
date-released: 2026-04-15
